definition.value: A composition-only glycan consisting of one hexosyl group, one acetaminohexosyl group, one hexuronic acid group and one sulfate group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex1 HexNAc1 HexA1 S1.
A composition-only glycan consisting of one acetaminohexosyl group and two 6-deoxyhexosyl groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: HexNAc1 dHex2.
An organic heterotricyclic compound that is any benzimidazole ortho-fused to a pyridine ring.
An inhibitor which inhibits the action of ferroptosis suppressor protein 1.
A 2-amino-4-(S-butylsulfonimidoyl)butanoic acid which has R-configuration.
A group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of 6-(2,6-bis[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl]-alpha-D-mannosyl)-beta-D-mannose.
A non-proteinogenic alpha-amino acid that is homocysteine in which the thiol group carries an oxo, imino and butyl groups.
A thyroxine sulfate(1-) that has L-configuration. The major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of cyclobutanes that is ((14)C)cyclobutane which carries a carboxy, amino and fluoro groups at positions 1, 1 and 3, respectively (the 1r,3r-stereoisomer).

An organoselenium compound that is diselane covalently bound to two methyl groups. It has been detected in onion-family vegetables and soft-necked garlics. It induces ER stress and toxic protein aggregation in the budding yeast, S. cerevisiae and used as a reagent to identify distonic radical cations.
A doubly-charged L-alpha-amino acid anion resulting from deprotonation of both carboxy groups of 3-hydroxy-L-glutamic acid.

A composition-only glycan consisting of seven hexosyl groups, six acetaminohexosyl groups, one 6-deoxyhexosyl group, three N-acetyl-neuraminic acid groups and one N-glycolyl-neuraminic acid group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex7 HexNAc6 dHex1 NeuAc3 NeuGc1.

A composition-only glycan consisting of seven hexosyl groups, five acetaminohexosyl groups and three N-acetyl-neuraminic acid groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex7 HexNAc5 NeuAc3.
A branched amino octasaccharide correspnding to the inner core and outer core moieties of the bacterial O-SP--core antigen of Vibrio cholerae O1, serotype Ogawa.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is a henicosasaccharide derivative consisting of a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man linear hexasaccharide group via a (1->3) linkage and a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-[beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man branched undecasaccharide group via a (1->6) linkage, while to the N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue at the reducing end is linked (1->6) an alpha-L-fucose residue.
A 3-sulfopropanediol(1-) that has S-configuration.
An organosulfonate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 3-oxopropane-1-sulfonic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of furans that is furan in which the hydrogen at position 2 is replaced by a nonyl group.
A substance to which an electron may be transferred.
A very long-chain fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any omega-methyl-very-long-chain fatty acid; major species at pH 7.3.
An omega-hydroxy fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any omega-hydroxy-very-long-chain fatty acid; major species at pH 7.3.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is a tetracosasaccharide derivative consisting of a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-Man and two beta-D-GlcNAc residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked a beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man linear heptasaccharide group via a (1->3) linkage and a beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man branched tridecasaccharide group via a (1->6) linkage, while to the beta-D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end is linked (1->6) an alpha-L-Fuc residue.

An amino oligosaccharide that is a heptacosasaccharide derivative consisting of a trisaccharide of beta-D-Man and two beta-D-GlcNAc residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the Man residue of which are linked a beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man heptasaccharide group via a (1->3) linkage and a beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man tridecasaccharide group via a (1->6) linkage, while to the beta-D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end is linked (1->6) an alpha-L-Fuc residue.
An N-glycoloylneuraminate that is conjugate base of N-glycoloyl-alpha-neuraminic acid arising from the deprotonation of the carboxy group. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
The (R)-enantiomer of mandelic acid.

An amino oligosaccharide that is a triacontasaccharide derivative consisting of a trisaccharide of beta-D-Man and two beta-D-GlcNAc residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the Man residue of which are linked a beta-D-Gal-(1-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1-3)-beta-D-Gal-(1-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1-3)-beta-D-Gal-(1-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1-3)-beta-D-Gal-(1-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1-2)-alpha-D-Man linear nonasaccharide group via a (1->3) linkage and a beta-D-Gal-(1-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1-3)-beta-D-Gal-(1-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1-3)-beta-D-Gal-(1-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1-3)-beta-D-Gal-(1-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1-2)-[beta-D-Gal-(1-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1-3)-beta-D-Gal-(1-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1-3)-beta-D-Gal-(1-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1-3)-beta-D-Gal-(1-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1-6)]-alpha-D-Man branched heptadecasaccharide group via a (1->6) linkage, while to the beta-D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end is linked (1->6) an alpha-L-Fuc residue.
A methyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of phloretic acid with methanol. It is a nitrification inhibitor and a plant growth regulator.
A minor stable isotope of calcium with relative atomic mass 42.95877 and 0.135 atom percent natural abundance.
An oxidized N-acyl-gamma-aminobutyric acid obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A tetracyclic diterpenoid with formula C20H30O4. It is a nitrification inhibitor isolated from root exudates of Brachiaria humidicola.
A stable isotope of molybdenum with relative atomic mass 97.90541, 24.29 atom percent natural abundance and nuclear spin 0.
A major stable isotope of strontium with relative atomic mass 87.90561 and 82.58 atom percent natural abundance.
A stable isotope of rubidium with relative atomic mass 84.91179, 72.17 atom percent natural abundance and nuclear spin 5/2.
A stable isotope of selenium with relative atomic mass 81.91670, 8.82 atom percent natural abundance and nuclear spin 0.
A stable isotope of zinc with relative atomic mass 65.92603, 27.7 atom percent natural abundance and nuclear spin 0.
